CICERO TO TIRO Cumae, April 152, 54 or 53 13.c.

Aegypta⁶ joined me here on April Ich. Al-l though he reported that you were entirely rid of your fever and were going on nicely, yet his telling me that you had been unable to write caused rne some anxiety 3 and all the more so, because Hermia,d who ought to have arrived on the same day, has not done so. You could not believe how anxious I am about your health: if you relieve me from that anxiety, I will relieve you of all your duties.
